Start a new cluster:
minikube start

Deploy the Prometheus Operator:
helm repo add prometheus-community https://prometheus-community.github.io/helm-charts
helm install my-monitoring prometheus-community/kube-prometheus-stack

Deploy your application:
helm install my-kusama-monitor ./my-kusama-monitor

Access the Prometheus and AlertManager UIs through port forwarding or by retrieving the service URLs.

Monitor logs and alerts as needed.


Useful commands:

To initialize a new project:
npm init -y 

Install the necessary dependencies:
npm install --save @polkadot/api dotenv typescript
npm install --save-dev ts-node

Run the application:
npm start


Terminal output after running the application:

 % npm start

> kusama-monitor@1.0.0 start
> ts-node index.ts

Connected to wss://kusama-rpc.polkadot.io/


Initialize a new Helm chart in your project directory:
helm create my-kusama-monitor
